WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:10.810
This Core edition explains the common structure for client onboarding. The model connects five elements: source evidence

2
00:00:10.810 --> 00:00:21.259
and where it came from; client identity and the people involved; requested services and engagement facts; open requests

3
00:00:21.259 --> 00:00:31.269
with their next actions; and dates and history maintained over time. The elements remain distinct but connected,

4
00:00:31.269 --> 00:00:41.279
so every fact can be traced to the document or decision behind it. Country implementations make the

5
00:00:41.279 --> 00:00:51.728
model operational by mapping their own documents, checks and rules onto these stable fields. The conceptual result is

6
00:00:51.728 --> 00:00:59.200
a readable structure for understanding what is known, what remains open and how the client file develops.
